@page "/introduction"
@inject NavigationManager NavigationManager

<PageTitle>Dashboard</PageTitle>
<MudText Typo="Typo.h4" Class="my-2">
    <MudIcon Icon="fas fa-info" />
    Introduction
</MudText>

<MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-2">
    This is an application which demonstrates generation of dynamic forms in Blazor WebAssembly 
    using a configuration and then collection of submitted form data by the user. Application's 
    sidebar menu can be toggled by clicking the hamburger icon on top left.
</MudText>

<MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-4">
    For the purpose of simplicity, we will be allowing user to define a dynamic form by providing
    its configuration in JSON format and the data submitted by the user will also be collected as
    a JSON object.
</MudText>

<MudText Typo="Typo.body1" Class="mb-2">
    The whole process is divided in below mentioned three steps.
</MudText>

<MudCard Class="mb-4">
    <MudCardHeader>
        <CardHeaderContent>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">Step 1</MudText>
        </CardHeaderContent>
    </MudCardHeader>
    <MudCardContent>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">Define the form configuration as JSON.</MudText>
    </MudCardContent>
    <MudCardActions>
        <MudButton 
            Variant="Variant.Text" 
            Color="Color.Primary" 
            StartIcon="fas fa-code" 
            onclick="Step1">Define</MudButton>
    </MudCardActions>
</MudCard>

<MudCard Class="mb-4">
    <MudCardHeader>
        <CardHeaderContent>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">Step 2</MudText>
        </CardHeaderContent>
    </MudCardHeader>
    <MudCardContent>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">
            Present Form (also known as render form) based on the form configuration provided in step 1. 
            Allow user to submit data after validating it.
        </MudText>
    </MudCardContent>
    <MudCardActions>
        <MudButton 
            Variant="Variant.Text" 
            Color="Color.Primary" 
            StartIcon="fas fa-desktop" 
            OnClick="Step2">Present</MudButton>
    </MudCardActions>
</MudCard>

<MudCard Class="mb-4">
    <MudCardHeader>
        <CardHeaderContent>
            <MudText Typo="Typo.h6">Step 3</MudText>
        </CardHeaderContent>
    </MudCardHeader>
    <MudCardContent>
        <MudText Typo="Typo.body2">View gathered form data submitted by user in step 2 as JSON.</MudText>
    </MudCardContent>
    <MudCardActions>
        <MudButton 
            Variant="Variant.Text" 
            Color="Color.Primary" 
            StartIcon="fas fa-keyboard" 
            OnClick="Step3">Gathered Data</MudButton>
    </MudCardActions>
</MudCard>
